Another important aspect of #ChatGPT is its ability to handle long-term dependencies in conversations. It uses a combination of techniques, such as RNNs and self-attention mechanisms, to keep track of the context and maintain coherence over the course of the conversation.(5/7)
Can't get enough of #ChatGPT, feels ureal!

One key aspect of the #ChatGPT architecture is the use of persona tokens, which are added to the input sequence to represent the chatbot's persona. They help the model maintain persona throughout the conversation and provide additional context for generating responses.(4/7)

#ChatGPT uses self-attention mechanisms to process input, taking into account the context of the conversation and the persona of the chatbot. It then generates a response by predicting the next word in the sequence, using the same information to guide the generation process.(3/7)

#ChatGPT is based on the transformer architecture, which uses self-attention mechanisms to process input sequences. However,It has been modified to better handle the specific challenges of chatbot conversations, such as handling context and maintaining a consistent persona. (2/7)

What would be a tragedy here, IMO, is the possibility that #ChatGPT will become yet another tool to generate random text that enables bots, plagiarists, and more. It would be sad if the results it produced were accepted without question.

I think that a path to productivity from this point on for #ChatGPT may be a kind of productionization of this model for search, learning and such tasks that nudges users towards doing their own research. This may be better in the long run too.

I asked ChatGPT to do my job
#ChatGPT #OpenAI #OpenAIChatGPT  https://t.co/vDM8PqE0ww

#ChatGPT also seems to be great at picking up context. This is not surprising since it is a transformer model, but it is great to see in action nevertheless. Longer chats where it infers stuff from past responses and questions are revelatory about its capabilities.

#ChatGPT also seems to answer a broad range of kinds of questions and asks - exposition on a given topic, comparative analyses and critiques from different perspectives of a topic, generation of code, explaining the detail of a specific line of code, etc.

#ChatGPT does well at multimodality within the text format. It is able to go between prose, poetry of different kinds - ballads, sonnets, and limericks, paras of scientific text, bulleted lists suitable for a presentation or report, mathematical equations... in one chat.

What #ChatGPT does great at is in condensing a voluminous topic into a pointed, specific response. And it does this consistently well. I was surprised by how some responses were more concise, and others were lengthier.

I'm thoroughly impressed by how effectively I was able to research a topic in a conversational setting - the experience is just way better than having a gazillion tabs open and scatterbrained link following, followed by note-taking. #ChatGPT
